  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective, controlled, opened randomized study to evaluate the cost benefit of a
      primary implantation of a loop recorder versus the conventional diagnostic cascade for
      syncope most likely due to cardiac arrhythmia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
